WEBVTT

00:29.730 --> 00:29.970
Hello.

00:30.531 --> 00:35.535
Welcome to God Day, and this is Derek Walker, the pastor of the Oxford Bible Church.

00:35.636 --> 00:36.536
Good to be with you.

00:37.297 --> 00:42.502
I want to share today on the wonderful subject of messianic prophecy.

00:43.203 --> 00:49.208
That is, all the prophecies of the Messiah, the coming Messiah, from the beginning of time.

00:50.329 --> 00:59.538
Once man fell, God began giving a portrait of the coming champion, God's champion, the Messiah, who would

00:59.650 --> 01:06.623
save mankind and ultimately restore mankind to in the kingdom of God.

01:06.683 --> 01:13.776
And Messianic prophecy is one of the wonderful proofs that the Bible is the word of God.

01:13.836 --> 01:23.794
I remember when I became a Christian, I heard the message and I thought this is so amazing that God became a man in the person of Jesus Christ.

01:24.514 --> 01:32.102
And then I studied for the evidence of it and studied the evidence of the resurrection.

01:33.103 --> 01:43.373
And one thing that was also very convincing to me was all the prophecies, these messianic prophecies that Jesus fulfilled in his life.

01:43.473 --> 01:44.194
It was amazing.

01:44.874 --> 01:47.577
And we don't have time to get into all of those now.

01:48.198 --> 01:52.402
But I want to share some key principles

01:52.834 --> 01:55.456
to help you understand messianic prophecy.

01:56.177 --> 01:58.800
And one of them is called the sufferings and the glory.

01:59.580 --> 02:09.530
Basically, there are two different types of vision of the coming Messiah that is given in the Old Testament and in the prophets.

02:11.952 --> 02:15.615
The coming Messiah is described in two very different ways.

02:17.597 --> 02:21.641
First, that he would come in humility as a suffering servant.

02:21.701 --> 02:22.642
He would come to

02:22.722 --> 02:26.406
to suffer and die for our sins and for our salvation.

02:27.367 --> 02:36.417
And then there's another set of prophecies that describe him coming in power and glory as the king, the conquering king to reign on earth.

02:36.978 --> 02:37.798
Totally different.

02:38.459 --> 02:50.592
And when those prophecies are together, if you read it carefully, it's always the suffering Messiah first and then the glorious Messiah, not the other way around.

02:51.533 --> 02:52.114
And so

02:52.194 --> 03:01.263
These prophets saw his sufferings as our Savior and his glory, the glory that would follow as our King.

03:01.924 --> 03:07.930
But it didn't define what kind of time period would be between those two.

03:07.970 --> 03:19.602
Now, we know that actually Jesus fulfilled these two things through his two comings, which are about at least, anyway, 2,000 years apart.

03:20.130 --> 03:26.278
He came the first time to suffer for our sin, and he'll come the second time as the glorious king.

03:26.938 --> 03:32.866
And these images are so different that some Jews actually believe that there'd be two messiahs.

03:33.026 --> 03:40.535
One would call the son of Joseph, who would be the suffering messiah, who would then ultimately be exalted.

03:40.555 --> 03:49.426
And then the other one, they would call the son of David, who, like David, would be a conquering king.

03:49.858 --> 04:09.428
Actually, though, the New Testament makes it clear that there is only one Messiah, but Jesus, and he will fulfill both aspects of the Messiah because he comes twice, the first time as the suffering Messiah, the second time as the conquering King.

04:10.830 --> 04:18.802
And this two-fold nature of the Messiah corresponds actually to the two-fold program of God,

04:18.882 --> 04:25.332
or the two programs of God, which I call the salvation program and the kingdom program.

04:25.372 --> 04:33.385
So throughout history, God is fulfilling two programs, salvation and kingdom.

04:34.026 --> 04:42.560
And a lot of people, when they read the Bible, they just think in terms of God's salvation and they ignore the large parts of the Bible that are about God's kingdom.

04:43.201 --> 04:46.546
So I want to unpack that, you see, to understand

04:47.010 --> 04:48.852
the kingdom program.

04:49.172 --> 04:50.954
That's actually what comes first.

04:52.096 --> 05:04.809
Originally God set up his kingdom and created the angels including Lucifer but then Lucifer rebelled against God, rebelled against God and set up his counter kingdom.

05:04.870 --> 05:16.242
He took a third of the angels with him and so you've got this kingdom of darkness based on the lie and then God creates man.

05:16.482 --> 05:23.872
in his image and to actually exercise dominion on the earth.

05:23.932 --> 05:35.227
That man's purpose is to be in God's kingdom, under God's authority and imaging God, expressing God's nature and dominion in the earth.

05:35.828 --> 05:40.114
And so man was to be part of God's kingdom program and

05:40.226 --> 05:46.656
God's vision, as it were, was that his kingdom would cover the earth as man multiplied.

05:47.418 --> 05:55.270
But man sinned and joined the enemy's kingdom and came under the kingdom of darkness.

05:55.972 --> 06:07.410
And since then, there's been a war between God's kingdom and Satan's kingdom consisting of all those in rebellion against God.

06:09.026 --> 06:13.050
The important thing to understand is that God is not a softie or a loser.

06:13.851 --> 06:17.234
He has not changed his kingdom purpose and program.

06:17.675 --> 06:23.741
He is still going to establish his kingdom on the earth and put all his enemies under foot.

06:24.021 --> 06:31.228
You know, you can see that in Psalm 8, because Psalm 8 was written by David 3,000 years after the fall of man.

06:32.129 --> 06:37.074
And so you might think God's ideal idea has failed.

06:37.570 --> 06:43.257
You know, God wanted to establish His kingdom on earth, but man sinned, now it's all a mess.

06:44.038 --> 06:49.605
But 3,000 years later, the psalm 8 is written as if the fall has not even happened.

06:49.865 --> 06:52.909
God's purpose is still the same.

06:53.850 --> 06:57.875
Psalm 8, verse 4, it says, What is man that you are mindful of him?

06:58.716 --> 07:00.458
Or the son of man that you visit him?

07:01.139 --> 07:04.022
For you have made him a little lower than the angels.

07:04.663 --> 07:07.026
You have crowned him with glory and honour.

07:07.298 --> 07:11.984
And you have made him to have dominion over the works of your hands.

07:12.124 --> 07:14.387
You have put all things under his feet.

07:14.987 --> 07:18.071
So God's kingdom program is still in place.

07:19.012 --> 07:21.095
We aren't called to rule and reign with God.

07:21.976 --> 07:32.889
And therefore, this is the first program of God is his kingdom program in which his kingdom is advancing step by step through the ages.

07:33.851 --> 07:36.594
And it's going to be fulfilled through the Messiah.

07:36.802 --> 07:41.991
and ultimately all his enemies are going to be put under his feet.

07:43.012 --> 07:48.021
Now, people say, you know, why does God allow all this evil to happen?

07:48.702 --> 07:53.991
God could have judged his enemies and destroyed the kingdom of darkness immediately.

07:54.772 --> 07:56.715
But why is he delayed doing that?

07:56.996 --> 07:58.879
Why does he allow evil to continue?

07:59.781 --> 08:03.026
And the reason is that he

08:03.170 --> 08:05.152
brought in his salvation program.

08:05.192 --> 08:13.862
You see, when man's ined, if God would have immediately applied his kingdom program and judged mankind, then that would be the end of us.

08:13.922 --> 08:15.164
There would be no hope for us.

08:15.584 --> 08:25.696
But because God loved us, he put in place a second program called his salvation program that he would accomplish through the Messiah.

08:26.477 --> 08:27.698
But that would take time.

08:27.970 --> 08:35.261
We'll take time to prepare the way for the coming of the Messiah, for the Messiah to die and rise again and purchase our salvation.

08:35.602 --> 08:41.992
And then for Him to call people to repentance and to put their trust in the Messiah.

08:42.493 --> 08:51.427
And so God held back His kingdom program in order for the salvation program to work and save as many people as possible.

08:51.767 --> 08:56.114
But ultimately, God is going to fulfill His kingdom program

08:56.258 --> 09:00.622
Christ will return and establish his kingdom on the earth.

09:00.663 --> 09:02.905
So there are two programs working together.

09:02.925 --> 09:13.416
He wants to save as many as possible from destruction and he is going to establish his kingdom on the earth.

09:13.996 --> 09:22.065
And that's why it says in 2 Peter 3.9, God, the Lord is not slack concerning his promise to establish his kingdom on the earth.

09:22.645 --> 09:23.506
As some count

09:23.586 --> 09:32.018
slackness, but is long suffering toward us, not willing that any should perish, but that all should come to repentance.

09:32.038 --> 09:53.490
And so God is holding back his judgment and his kingdom in order to save as many people as possible, because when he actually does move in his kingdom power, then those who have not turned to him yet will actually come under judgment and then they will have no more hope of receiving salvation.

09:54.018 --> 10:08.361
And so that's why Jesus had to first come as the suffering Messiah to fulfill the salvation program and make it possible for mankind to be saved before he comes in his glory.

10:08.821 --> 10:14.250
So you see the two programs relate to the two aspects of the Messiah, his suffering and his glory.

10:14.651 --> 10:20.600
And that's why the suffering for salvation has to happen before his coming in glory.

10:21.261 --> 10:21.842
And so

10:21.954 --> 10:26.602
That's why Jesus said, you know, when he rose from the dead, they didn't really understand.

10:26.662 --> 10:35.717
The Jews were looking for the concrete Messiah because they were oppressed by the Romans.

10:36.398 --> 10:48.658
So they weren't thinking that they needed a Messiah to save them from their sin, especially because they come under a false teaching of Phariseeism, legalism.

10:49.314 --> 10:52.457
which gave the impression that you can save yourself by your works.

10:53.619 --> 10:56.922
And so they thought, we just need to keep the law.

10:56.982 --> 11:01.287
We don't need a, you know, we don't need a savior, a personal savior.

11:01.327 --> 11:05.211
And they didn't realize that that was their main need.

11:05.811 --> 11:11.678
All they saw is they need a political savior, a political messiah, who could save them from the Romans.

11:11.758 --> 11:15.922
And that's one reason they didn't recognize Jesus when he came.

11:16.162 --> 11:21.809
in his resurrection, even though his disciples were not understanding this.

11:22.830 --> 11:28.217
And so he rebukes them in the resurrection that they haven't studied the Scripture well enough.

11:28.617 --> 11:44.316
He said in Luke 24, 25, he says, oh, foolish ones, slow of heart to believe in all that the prophets have spoken, or not the Christ, the Messiah, to first have suffered these things.

11:45.057 --> 11:45.618
Notice

11:45.698 --> 11:53.529
He first needs to suffer these things and then to enter into his glory.

11:54.050 --> 11:58.856
So he says, the glory will come, but first I had to suffer these things.

11:59.337 --> 12:06.748
The beginning of Moses and all the script prophets, he expounded to them in all the scriptures, the things concerning himself.

12:07.949 --> 12:14.258
And so Jesus is here claiming to be the suffering and the glorious Messiah.

12:14.530 --> 12:17.774
but that he had to suffer first, be raised from the dead.

12:17.934 --> 12:21.499
And then he would enter his glory.

12:22.200 --> 12:37.138
And so he later said in Luke 24, about verse 45 to 47, he said, it is written and it was necessary for the Christ to suffer and then rise from the dead.

12:37.378 --> 12:42.947
the third day and that repentance and remission of sins should be preached in his name.

12:43.427 --> 12:56.748
So in other words, the salvation program requires that the Messiah must first suffer and die and that then the gospel go out to the nation so that people have a chance to be saved.

12:57.770 --> 13:05.682
And so this is how we understand messianic prophecy.

13:06.242 --> 13:11.029
Some of the prophecies are to do with his first coming in humility.

13:11.690 --> 13:16.397
Other prophecies are to do with his second coming in power and glory.

13:17.018 --> 13:27.334
The Jews missed it because they were looking for the glorious Messiah when, of course, he had to first of all come as the suffering Messiah.

13:28.155 --> 13:32.481
And so notice he says, you need to read all the scriptures.

13:33.062 --> 13:35.666
See, there's a tendency, isn't there, even with us?

13:35.842 --> 13:40.527
and the Jews did the same thing, you cherry-pick the verses you like.

13:41.068 --> 13:51.100
So they chose the verses about the conquering Messiah that suited them, and they ignored passages and still do, sadly, like Isaiah 53.

13:51.160 --> 13:57.668
That talk about the suffering Messiah, the Savior from our sins.

13:58.428 --> 14:03.154
And they ignored that.

14:03.234 --> 14:06.479
When we read the Bible, we must read it systematically.

14:06.519 --> 14:13.569
We mustn't just cherry-pick the bits we like, because that's how they actually, they missed it.

14:14.711 --> 14:23.424
And so Jesus, he came, first of all, to die for our sins.

14:24.345 --> 14:32.818
And Christians often just focus on that, and they ignore the other prophecies, which are the kingdom prophecies.

14:32.930 --> 14:42.303
that the same Jesus who died for our sins is actually going to come again in power and glory and establish his kingdom on the earth.

14:43.024 --> 14:45.427
And he will reign on earth for a thousand years.

14:46.168 --> 14:52.217
And even from the fourth century, third and fourth, fourth century, the church rejected that idea.

14:52.497 --> 14:57.744
They thought, well, all the prophecies of the kingdom are fulfilled in the church age.

14:58.305 --> 15:01.970
There is no future kingdom of God on earth.

15:02.146 --> 15:04.409
they rejected the prophecy.

15:04.429 --> 15:06.611
So they accepted, they did the opposite of the Jews.

15:06.651 --> 15:12.137
They accepted the prophecies of the suffering saviour, but then they rejected the kingdom prophecies.

15:12.518 --> 15:14.800
But Jesus would rebuke that.

15:15.241 --> 15:17.143
He would say, foolish ones.

15:17.964 --> 15:23.570
You must believe all the Scriptures concerning the Messiah.

15:23.590 --> 15:30.738
So because we're so aware of our need for salvation, we can assume the whole Bible is about salvation.

15:31.266 --> 15:33.509
and miss God's kingdom program.

15:34.210 --> 15:40.377
Actually, God's kingdom program, you can only understand the Bible in terms of God's kingdom program first.

15:41.338 --> 15:43.561
That's God's original purpose for man.

15:44.502 --> 15:48.107
And when sin came in, it disrupted that.

15:49.629 --> 15:59.220
And so that called forth the salvation program, which is designed to bring man back into God's kingdom.

15:59.801 --> 16:00.562
So

16:00.706 --> 16:08.737
that we can fulfill God's original purpose of us ruling and reigning with Him as God's image, representing Him.

16:09.819 --> 16:22.777
So the salvation program is a temporary addition to the kingdom program, but the kingdom program will continue forever and ever as God completes His kingdom purposes.

16:23.678 --> 16:29.586
And so the purpose of salvation is to restore that man

16:29.698 --> 16:31.641
back into his kingdom.

16:32.201 --> 16:39.672
And so this tells us that sin is essentially rebellion against God's authority, against his kingdom.

16:40.213 --> 16:42.396
That caused us to be kicked out of his kingdom.

16:42.836 --> 16:55.634
So therefore, to be truly saved requires repentance from our rebellion against God's authority and a submission to Jesus as Lord.

16:56.066 --> 17:11.365
So the two sides of the coin of salvation is, first of all, trusting in Christ as our Savior, who has purchased our salvation and provided the free pardon that we need to wipe the past clean.

17:11.886 --> 17:20.837
We have to trust in Him as our Savior, and there's a repentance there, I suppose, of we must repent of trusting in our own works for salvation.

17:21.618 --> 17:24.562
But also, there is a submission.

17:24.834 --> 17:26.375
to Christ as our Lord.

17:26.436 --> 17:30.519
We've got to be able to say from our heart, Jesus is my Lord.

17:31.200 --> 17:39.048
And that is the faith that brings us back into God's kingdom when we are submitted under his authority.

17:39.708 --> 17:40.269
Praise God.

17:40.589 --> 17:41.730
That's a saving faith.

17:42.591 --> 17:54.002
Some kind of faith, some kind of mental ascent that just says, well, I agree with the gospel and that Jesus, the Son of God, but there's no submission of the heart.

17:54.562 --> 17:57.446
is not a saving faith.

17:57.726 --> 17:58.868
Demons have that faith.

17:59.549 --> 18:04.656
You know, saving faith involves a submission to the Lordship of Christ.

18:05.116 --> 18:10.464
And so that is why we talk about Jesus being Lord and Savior.

18:11.104 --> 18:18.194
And so both these programs actually center in the Messiah

18:18.402 --> 18:30.400
and the original prophecy called the proto-evangelium in Genesis 3.15 took place immediately after the fall of man when God then announced to the devil.

18:30.800 --> 18:39.153
He said, Genesis 3.15, I will put enmity between you Satan and the woman and between your seed and her seed.

18:39.693 --> 18:48.306
So there will be a spiritual warfare between the seed of Satan, that's all those in his kingdom, angels, demons and people who are

18:48.514 --> 18:59.425
of their father, the devil, who are in rebellion against God, who are embraced the lie of Satan that we are autonomous, not created by God.

18:59.485 --> 19:00.566
We are our own God.

19:01.567 --> 19:05.931
And on the other side is her seed, the seed of the woman.

19:05.972 --> 19:10.196
That's the title of the Messiah, predicting that he would be born of a virgin.

19:10.696 --> 19:16.402
And also in that, you could see yourself, if you're in Christ, you are in

19:17.090 --> 19:18.051
the seed of the woman.

19:18.091 --> 19:19.212
You are in Christ.

19:19.813 --> 19:24.077
And so there's this battle between God's kingdom and Satan's kingdom.

19:24.437 --> 19:27.600
