27:04.578 --> 27:06.541
But let me just focus on two of them.

27:07.062 --> 27:16.416
One of the covenants that developed from the Abrahamic covenant is the new covenant that Jesus brought for our salvation.

27:16.837 --> 27:22.165
And through the new covenant in the blood of Jesus, we have salvation.

27:22.245 --> 27:28.114
That's the suffering messiah, fulfilling the salvation program of God.

27:28.290 --> 27:30.934
And there was another covenant that God made with David.

27:30.954 --> 27:39.909
It's called the Davidic covenant that promised that there would be an everlasting son of David who would have an everlasting kingdom on earth.

27:40.009 --> 27:42.894
And he would reign from the throne of David in Jerusalem.

27:43.435 --> 27:44.897
That's the Davidic covenant.

27:45.698 --> 27:50.306
And that will be fulfilled through the, that's the kingdom program.

27:50.386 --> 27:54.312
That will be fulfilled through Jesus in the second coming.

27:54.673 --> 27:55.474
He will come.

27:55.778 --> 28:01.611
and he will reign over the earth from the throne of David in fulfillment of the Davidic covenant.

28:01.631 --> 28:07.965
And so Jesus fulfills all the prophecies of the suffering Messiah and the glorious Kingly Messiah.

28:08.667 --> 28:10.130
Praise to Jesus, amen.

